# Agent Operating Model

This project uses a five-agent operating model orchestrated by the
`software-engineering-orchestrator` skill via the AI Task MCP server.

## Roles

- Requirements & Scope Agent: `requirement-to-story-spec`, `quality-attribute-accessibility-planner`.
- Architecture & API Agent: `system-design-adr-generator`, `api-contract-designer`.
- Implementation Agent: `change-plan-task-slicer`, `safe-code-generator-refactoring-engineer`.
- Verification & Security Agent: `test-strategy-composer`, `threat-model-secure-review`.
- Delivery & Reliability Agent: `supply-chain-release-gate`, `observability-slo-incident-improvement`.

## Routing Order

requirements -> quality -> architecture -> API -> implementation planning ->
code/refactor -> testing -> security -> release -> observability.

## Apply Boundary

- MCP produces proposal artifacts only.
- `approved -> applied` is a human action in Cursor unless an explicitly
  authorized automation token is permitted by policy.
- `applied -> closed` requires post-apply verifier results to pass.

## Skill Fallback

If a required skill is unavailable, the task is set to `blocked` with reason,
an audit event is emitted, and a recommendation appears in the quality
dashboard. Silent degradation is forbidden.
